BEGIN_PGML
Use the order of operations to evaluate

[```\definecolor{sapphire}{RGB}{59,90,125}\newcommand{\abs}[1]{\left\lvert#1\right\rvert}
              \dfrac{3^{3-1}+3\abs{9-10}}{\sqrt{3+18\div3}}
            \text{.}```]

[_]{3}{15}

END_PGML

############################################################
# Solution
############################################################

BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION
We start by identifying the innermost, highest priority operations:

[```\definecolor{sapphire}{RGB}{59,90,125}\newcommand{\abs}[1]{\left\lvert#1\right\rvert}\newcommand{\highlight}[1]{\mathchoice{\colorbox{lightsapphire}{$\displaystyle #1$}}{\colorbox{lightsapphire}{$\textstyle #1$}}{\colorbox{lightsapphire}{$\scriptstyle #1$}}{\colorbox{lightsapphire}{$\scriptscriptstyle #1$}}}\newcommand{\nextoperation}[1]{\mathord{\boxed{#1}}}\newcommand{\amp}{&}
\begin{aligned}
\frac{3^{3-1}+3\abs{9-10}}{\sqrt{3+18\div3}}\amp=\frac{3^{\nextoperation{3-1}}+3\abs{\nextoperation{9-10}}}{\sqrt{3+\nextoperation{18\div3}}}\\
\amp=\frac{3^{\highlight{2}}+3\nextoperation{\abs{\highlight{-1}}}}{\sqrt{\nextoperation{3+\highlight{6}}}}\\
\amp=\frac{\nextoperation{3^2}+3(\highlight{1})}{\sqrt{\highlight{9}}}\\
\amp=\frac{\highlight{9}+\nextoperation{3(1)}}{\nextoperation{\sqrt{9}}}\\
\amp=\frac{\nextoperation{9+\highlight{3}}}{\highlight{3}}\\
\amp=\frac{\highlight{12}}{3}=\highlight{4}
\end{aligned}
```]

END_PGML_SOLUTION

